author: fitz
msg: Begin work on implementing the behaviors of the svn:needs-lock
property: Prevent it from being set on directories, canonicalize its
value to '*', and flip its file to read/write when it is deleted.
* includes/svn_props.h (SVN_PROP_NEEDS_LOCK, SVN_PROP_NEEDS_LOCK_VALUE): New
defines.
* libsvn_wc/props.c (validate_prop_against_node_kind): Prevent
svn:needs-lock from being set on directories.
(svn_wc_prop_set2): Canonicalize the prop value to '*', and set it
to read-write if the property was deleted.
* io.c (svn_io_set_file_read_write_carefully): New function that
conservatively adds and removes write permissions from files.
(cache_default_file_perms): Private helper function.
(default_file_perms): Static variable for caching file perms.
* svn_io.h (svn_io_set_file_read_write_carefully): New function declaration.
